    <string name="about">
                            <![CDATA[
Chess Opener is an Open Source GNU GPL V2 Licence software.<br />
It consists in a chess game where you can learn chess openings while you play.<br />
You will have a library of chess openings so you can learn more about them. It will have a description, a bit of the moves history and a video that explains the moves.<br />
It has 2 game modes. PvP and PvE. In PvE you can practice against a AI and try the opening moves.
In PvP you can challenge one friend to play with you and use the openings to beat them.<br /><br />

Libraries used:<br />
- several Wikipedia chess openings information.<br />
- Jcarolus\' Chess<br />
- Android Support Library v4<br />
- Bumptech\'s Glide image loading library<br />
- Wikimedia creative commons images<br />
]]>
</string>

